  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 2.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The spirit of God came upon him.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " This seems to intimate a higher state of inspiration than the expression, \"God put a word into his mouth\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 23:5, 16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Numbers 24:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The third saying. - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 24:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 24:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". From the two revelations which he had received before, Balaam, saw, i.e., perceived, that it pleased Jehovah to bless Israel. This induced him not to go out for auguries, as on the previous occasions. כּפעם־בּפעם, \"as time after time,\" i.e., as at former times (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 23:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 23:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). He therefore turned his face to the desert, i.e., to the steppes of Moab, where Israel was encamped (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 22:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). And when he lifted up his eyes, \"he saw Israel encamping according to its tribes; and the Spirit of God came over him.\" The impression made upon him by the sight of the tribes of Israel, served as the subjective preparation for the reception of the Spirit of God to inspire him. Of both the earlier utterances it is stated that \"Jehovah put a word into his mouth\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 23:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 23:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); but of this third it is affirmed that \"the Spirit of God came over him.\" The former were communicated to him, when he went out for a divine revelation, without his being thrown into an ecstatic state; he heard the voice of God within him telling him what he was to say. But this time, like the prophets in their prophesyings, he was placed by the Spirit of God in a state of ecstatic sight; so that, with his eyes closed as in clairvoyance, he saw the substance of the revelation from God with his inward mental eye, which had been opened by the Spirit of God. Thus not only does he himself describe his own condition in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 24:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 24:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but his description is in harmony with the announcement itself, which is manifestly the result both in form and substance of the intuition effected within him by the Spirit of God. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]